import tensorflow as tf
import numpy as np
import cv2
from tensorflow.keras.applications.inception_v3 import InceptionV3
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing import image
from tensorflow.keras.applications.inception_v3 import preprocess_input, decode_predictions
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt


# Load InceptionV3 model
model = InceptionV3(weights='imagenet')

# Load and preprocess the image
img_path = r"C:\Users\charitha\Downloads\11.jpg"
img = image.load_img(img_path, target_size=(299, 299))
x = image.img_to_array(img)
x = np.expand_dims(x, axis=0)
x = preprocess_input(x)

print("Image shape:", x.shape)
print("Image min/max:", x.min(), x.max())

# ...
# Get the index of the predicted class
preds = model.predict(x)
predicted_class = np.argmax(preds[0])

print("Predicted class index:", predicted_class)
print("Top predicted classes:", decode_predictions(preds, top=3))

# Calculate gradients of the predicted class output with respect to the input image
with tf.GradientTape() as tape:
    x_tensor = tf.convert_to_tensor(x)  # Convert x to a TensorFlow tensor
    tape.watch(x_tensor)
    preds = model(x_tensor)
    class_output = preds[0][predicted_class]

# Calculate the gradient of the predicted class with respect to the input image
grads = tape.gradient(class_output, x_tensor)[0]

# Convert the gradients to a saliency map
saliency_map = np.max(np.abs(grads), axis=-1)

# Normalize the saliency map
saliency_map = (saliency_map - saliency_map.min()) / (saliency_map.max() - saliency_map.min())

# Resize the saliency map to the original image size
saliency_map = cv2.resize(saliency_map, (img.width, img.height))

# Convert the saliency map to a heatmap
heatmap = cv2.applyColorMap(np.uint8(255 * saliency_map), cv2.COLORMAP_JET)

# Convert the original image and the heatmap to NumPy arrays
original_image_np = np.array(img)
heatmap_np = np.array(heatmap)

# Combine the original image and the heatmap
saliency_image = cv2.addWeighted(original_image_np, 0.6, heatmap_np, 0.4, 0)

# Display the images
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

plt.subplot(131)
plt.imshow(original_image_np)
plt.title('Original Image')

plt.subplot(132)
plt.imshow(saliency_map, cmap='hot')
plt.title('Saliency Map')

plt.subplot(133)
plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(saliency_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
plt.title('Saliency Image')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
